      <outline text="iPhone Developer Site" MediaLinks="developer.apple.com—iphone &lt;http://developer.apple.com/iphone/&gt;">
        <outline text="Developers can create Web 2.0 applications that look and behave just like the applications built into iPhone, and provide seamless integration with iPhone applications and services including making a phone call, sending an email, and displaying a location in Google Maps. Third-party applications created using web standards can extend iPhones capabilities without compromising its reliability or security."/>
      </outline>
      <outline text="iWidgetgallery for iPhone widgets" MediaLinks="ipwid.com &lt;http://ipwid.com/&gt;">
        <outline text="Are you looking for iPhone widgets? Well, youre actually looking at one right now! Yes, our site is an iWidget. Just point your Safari to ipwid.com &lt;http://ipwid.com/&gt; and discover new widgets while youre on the go. Click here to preview what this page looks like on an iPhone!"/>
